macro_markets.query: What are the most important macroeconomic and stock market news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major index movements, Fed/central bank news, and significant company earnings or announcements.

items.title: US Stocks Decline Amid AI Disruption Fears
items.summary: S&P 500 and Nasdaq 100 both fell 1.4%, Dow Jones dropped 1.2% due to AI concerns spreading across sectors. Federal Reserve rate cut expectations shifted to July following strong non-farm payrolls data.

items.title: Hang Seng Closes Flat at 26,567 Amid Tech Selloff
items.summary: Hang Seng Index ended flat at 26,567 with major tech losses led by Meituan (-10.1%) and Kuaishou (-3.9%). WuXi Biologics gained 7.8% on strong earnings.

items.title: US PMI Manufacturing Surges into Expansion
items.summary: January PMI Manufacturing Index unexpectedly rose above 50, signaling expansion and reduced drag on US GDP growth. Combined with disinflation to 2.4% annual inflation, supports constructive outlook for equities and Fed easing.

items.title: Major Earnings Week Ahead with High Volatility Expectations
items.summary: Key companies reporting include PANW (+/-9.04%), WMT (+/-5.74%), and high-volatility names like HIVE (+/-16.74%) and CVNA (+/-15.52%). Options imply significant moves for tech, energy, and retail sectors.

items.title: Indian IT Stocks Plunge on AI Demand Concerns
items.summary: Infosys down 16.5%, TCS down 14%, HCL Tech down 14.2% as AI tools reduce service demands. India VIX stable near 13 amid mixed global cues.

crypto_news.query: What are the most significant cryptocurrency and blockchain news from the past 24 hours? Include major price movements, regulatory news, and notable project developments.

items.title: Major Token Unlocks Scheduled for February 17-20 Including YZY, LayerZero, and Kaito
items.summary: On February 17, YZY unlocks 62.5 million tokens worth $20.34 million (17.24% of released supply), while LayerZero and Kaito unlock 25.71 million ZRO and 32.6 million KAITO on February 20, respectively. Other unlocks like ZKsync, Solv Protocol, and ApeCoin are also expected in the third week of February.

items.title: Crypto Majors Slide into Extreme Fear Despite Bitcoin Holding Above $67K
items.summary: Crypto Fear and Greed Index drops to 12 amid weekly losses: Ethereum down 7.45% to $1,975, Solana down 3.64% to $84.70, BNB down 3.86% to $617, while Bitcoin trades near $67,950 after a 4.28% weekly decline.

items.title: Bitcoin, Ethereum, XRP, and Solana Extend Losses on Presidents' Day
items.summary: Bitcoin drops 0.3% to $69,190, Ethereum falls 1% to $1,997, XRP declines nearly 2% to $1.50, and Solana drops 2% to $86 amid a total market cap of $2.44 trillion, mirroring losses in gold and silver.

items.title: iShares Bitcoin ETP Issues 550,000 New Securities on London Stock Exchange
items.summary: iShares Bitcoin ETP admits 550,000 new securities to trading on February 17 at $6.84 each, offering fractional Bitcoin exposure with a reduced TER of 0.15% through 2026, available to UK retail investors post-FCA changes.

items.title: Bitcoin Plunges to $60,000 with Losses Exceeding $2 Billion
items.summary: Bitcoin's price decline to around $60,000 in February 2026 triggers major capitulation and over $2 billion in losses following sustained selling pressure.

ai_news.query: What are the most important artificial intelligence and machine learning news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include new model releases, company announcements, research breakthroughs, and industry trends.

items.title: PumasAI Releases Pumas 2.8 with Embedded AI for Pharmacometrics
items.summary: PumasAI announced Pumas version 2.8, integrating PumasAide AI coding agents for real-time modeling and new estimation methods like Monte Carlo Expectation Maximization to advance clinical pharmacology.

items.title: BIOPREVENT: AI Tool Predicts Transplant Complications
items.summary: Researchers developed BIOPREVENT, a machine learning tool using immune biomarkers and clinical data to predict chronic GVHD and mortality risks after stem cell transplants, outperforming traditional methods.

items.title: MIT AI Model Optimizes Protein Drug Manufacturing
items.summary: MIT engineers created an AI model that optimizes codon sequences for protein production in yeast, reducing development costs by learning biological principles like codon syntax and biophysical features.

items.title: Waystar's AltitudeAI Prevents $15.5B in Healthcare Denials
items.summary: Waystar received Inc. Best in Business recognition for AI, with AltitudeAI automating revenue cycle tasks, achieving 95% time savings and double-digit denial overturn improvements.

items.title: UN Calls for Verification of Frontier AI Models
items.summary: A UN University brief urges trusted verification systems for frontier AI to prevent an arms race, emphasizing compute-based methods and multilateral approaches amid geopolitical risks.

items.title: SoftBank and AMD Validate GPU Partitioning for AI
items.summary: SoftBank and AMD partnered to test AMD Instinct GPUs with partitioning technology for efficient next-generation AI infrastructure workloads.

items.title: LLM-DRS: AI Summarizes Disaster Building Damage
items.summary: UC Berkeley researchers introduced LLM-DRS, using large language models and vision tech to generate narrative summaries of structural damage from disaster images, aiding rapid assessments.

items.title: Modern SIEM Market to Hit $13.55B by 2029 on AI Demand
items.summary: The modern SIEM market is projected to reach $13.55 billion by 2029, fueled by AI integration, cloud-native platforms, and escalating cyber threats.

gaming.query: What are the most notable video game and gaming industry news from the past 24 hours? Include game releases, announcements, esports, and industry developments.

items.title: February 17 Video Game Releases: NORSE: Oath of Blood, Under The Island, and Age of Empires II: DE Expansion
items.summary: Three notable games launch today, February 17, 2026: NORSE: Oath of Blood offers Viking-themed turn-based combat and settlement-building, Under The Island focuses on exploration and mystery, and Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition – The Last Chieftains adds new civilizations and campaigns.

items.title: GTA 6 Release Rumors Point to November 19, 2026 After Further Delay from May
items.summary: Speculation grows around GTA 6's launch shifting from May 26 to November 19, 2026, amid Rockstar's history of delays and strategic updates, keeping fans eagerly awaiting official confirmation.

items.title: Sony Eyes Delay for Next-Gen PlayStation Amid AI-Driven Memory Chip Shortage
items.summary: Sony is reportedly considering postponing its next-generation PlayStation console due to surging demand for RAM and other components driven by AI technologies.

items.title: Styx: Blades of Greed Set for February 19 Release as Week's Highlight
items.summary: The stealth-action sequel Styx: Blades of Greed arrives February 19, 2026, promising refined mechanics and expanded level design, generating significant pre-launch excitement.

items.title: Stop Killing Games Campaign Heads to EU Commission on February 23
items.summary: Organizer Ross Scott announces the anti-game shutdown movement will present its case to the EU Commission on February 23, 2026, following recent updates.

tech_news.query: What are the most important technology news and developments from the past 24 hours? Include major product launches, company news, and significant tech industry developments. Exclude AI-specific news.

items.title: Social Media Trial Accuses Big Tech of Creating Addiction Machines
items.summary: A test-case jury trial in Los Angeles is targeting big tech companies like Meta for designing addictive features such as infinite scroll and autoplay. TikTok and Snapchat have settled, with Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg set to testify amid growing regulatory scrutiny in the EU.

items.title: US Productivity Growth Accelerates to 2.7% in 2025 Amid Tech Advances
items.summary: Revised US labor data shows a 2.7% productivity increase for 2025, nearly doubling the prior decade's average, with robust GDP growth despite fewer jobs added. This decoupling highlights potential impacts from technology on economic output.

items.title: Germany Named Country of Honour for Canada's ALL IN Tech Event 2026
items.summary: Canada's largest AI and technology event ALL IN has selected Germany as the Country of Honour for its 2026 edition in Montréal, featuring a dedicated pavilion to foster business collaborations between Canadian and German innovators.
